WHY THE SECOND SCRIPT.

By running this script, you are bake-in the solutions to the three main reasons Tomcat installations usually fail in a CI/CD pipeline:
	1. The "Remote Address Valve" Fix: Your script explicitly overwrites the context.xml with a version that has the restriction removed. No more 3-minute hangs.
	2. The Role Fix: It explicitly adds the manager-script role, which is the "key" Jenkins needs to talk to Tomcat via API.
The XML Integrity Fix: By using the cat <<'EOF' method, it ensures that special characters (like the $ in the Manager tag) are preserved exactly as Tomcat needs them, preventing the "Unit not found" or "Manager app crashed" errors.
